What is DevOps and Why DevOps is Important, etc
ANS: DevOps practices include continuous integration, continuous delivery, infrastructure as code, and monitoring and logging.
DevOps is important because it helps organizations deliver software faster, more reliably, and with higher quality. 
By breaking down silos between development and operations teams,
DevOps promotes collaboration and communication, which can increase efficiency and reduce errors.

What is Automation, Scaling, and Infrastructure
ANS: Automation refers to use the of technology to automate the task and process
scaling: Scaling refers to the ability of a system or application to handle increased workload or traffic
Infrastructure:refers to the underlying hardware and software components that support an application or system

